climbs.name: Yankee Buzzard
climbs.fa: Ben Strobel and Ian CB probably

content.description: From a sit climb the slabby arete.
content.location: Below the lookout on a Boulder forty or fifty feet down.  It faces downhill.

content.description: Sit start on large undercling feature. Work up the face using interesting and comfy holds.
content.location: In the talus field to the east of Vulture Lookout. Get to the Uplands Trail via the D'Arcy Buttress social trail at the top of the CCC. Hike east on the trail for 15 minutes until you reach a bench with the name "Dominika Rupniewski" on it. The talus field is to the right. This is the first problem you see when cutting down through the woods to access the field.

content.description: Stand start on good edges, climb up with big moves on great holds.

Possibly the first thing you will look down on walking to the Vulture Lookout East.  Start sitting matched on the left arete.  Move right through a slot, gaining good sidepulls, probably quite extended.  Work thin feet and fire off a long move and top out.  No feet or hands are used right of the right crack, and no holds left of the starting arete.. Sounds contrived but makes sense when you climb on it.. just climb the beautiful shield of rock.
From an obvious ledge system climb up and left out of the cave.  A left exit to Mockingjay (same start) and probably a little harder.
content.location: From the lookout looking out it is down and right.  On a Boulder next to the cliffline.  A couple minute walk from the lookout.

content.description: Start sitting with a jug.  Climb up and left through edges and slots and finish.
content.location: just right of Big Bird.  If standing at the lookout and looking out it is 100 feet right and 40 feet down the hill.

content.description: Start sitting with an obvious ledge system, probably hamhocking with the left hand.  After a tricky first sequence climb up and right out of the cave.  A lengthy Boulder problem for the lake.
content.location: If looking out from the lookout, it is down and right on a Boulder next to the cliffband that forms the ridge. A couple minute walk from the look out.

content.description: Sit start on low sidepull jug and right hand scoop. Traverse left behind the tree and continue up the arete.
content.protection: A few pads, the tree makes things a bit sketchy
content.location: Directly to the left of Big Bird

content.description: up the huge flake using the obvious holds
content.location: The boulder you stand on as you at the turn out for an overlook of vulture area.

content.description: Start on the shelf in the mini corridor. After a couple not so bad moves to nice edges, bust a big move to a crimp right then head right through the roof feature and top out as for Spiral Staircase, gaining the arete and mantling into the scoop.  Fun and funky.
content.protection: 3/4 pads.  A thin blubber style pad is nice.  You probably don’t want to chuff off the finish.

content.description: Start on the massive jug and climb straight up the committing arete. The right wall is off and traversing left to the face drops the grade to V1.
Pure and tricky..  Start matched from a stand in the obvious juggy undercling.  Climb the very clean arete.  A delicate and powerful problem.
content.location: 100 feet below the lookout.  About level with the Spiral Staircase Boulder and facing east.  Next to a large prominent large triangle boulder in the talus.  Not far from anything in the zone really..

content.description: Start from a sit, squeezing the supreme slabby feature with your left hand on the arete.  A few slaps, fancy footwork and a long pull will land you on top.
content.location: 100 feet down and right from the lookout.  Just east, at the same level and facing a majority of the other problems, i.e. the big year and spiral staircase.

content.description: Start matched low on a good ledge, climb up the left side of the arete on good edges.
Start the same as for Chicken Run but move right into a large side pull and climb up exiting the left side of the roof.

climbs.name: Big Bird
climbs.fa: Ian CB and Ben Strobel probably

content.description: Start matched on a slopey edge.  Climb through sidepulls and punch a big move to a jug.  Top out.
content.location: Looking out from the lookout, this is on a cliff band roughly 100 feet right and 40 feet downhill.  It faces downhill and the problem Plumage is right next to it.

content.description: From the jug start of Fire Escape, move left, gain the arete and continue on.  Grade unconfirmed and not graded on the FA.
Start standing with right hand edge left hand gaston.
A mostly sunny area with some quality Boulder problems so far and potential for more.  Very close to Vulture Lookout West and worth a visit.
